Figure Caption: The OIM maps showing the grain size evolution as a function of temperature at 1223K, 1348K and 1423K for different aging time periods (5min to 120min) in Al0.3CoCrFeNi alloy. The grain size distribution plots (area fraction (AF) on y axis vs grain size (μm) on x axis) is shown in the inset of each OIM map,
Vickers hardness (Hv) as a function of root squared grain size (μm−1/2) in the Al0.3CoCrFeNi alloy.

(a) Stress-strain plot from Al0.3CoCrFeNi alloy from three different grain sizes obtained by different times of aging at 1150°C after cold rolling as labeled (b) yield strength as a function of grain size.

(a and b)TEM SADP from [001]fccand [011]fcczone axis from solution aged (SA) condition (1150°C/60min) respectively (c) TEM-dark-field image recorded from a {001} superlattice reflection (marked on the inset diffraction pattern) in SA+550°C/150h condition (d) SEM BSED image from SA+700°C/50h condition from a grain boundary triple junction showing the lath like precipitates (Higher magnification image shown as an inset) (e) the bright field TEM image of the grain boundary and near grain boundary region lifted out from a rectangular region highlighted in (d) in SA+700°C/50h condition. (f)–(g) TEM SADP from [112]fccand [011]fcczone axis from a region highlighted in (e). (h) TEM-dark-field image recorded from a {001} superlattice reflection (marked on the inset diffraction pattern) in SA+700°C/150h condition. The SADP in inset can be consistently indexed as the [011] ZA diffraction pattern from a B2 phase.
Stress-strain plot from Al0.3CoCrFeNi alloy from three different heat treatment conditions as labeled in the figure.

X-ray diffraction results from synchrotron X-ray diffraction experiments on CR+1150°C/2min) and CR+1150°C/2min+620°C/50h samples as labeled in the figure. The insets on the right hand side of the X-ray plots show the BSE-SEM images taken from the same sample.
Stress-Strain plot from CR+1150°C/2min and CR+1150°C/2min+620°C/50h samples as labeled in the figure.
